Response to multiple hits from Protestor Spatz.<br>
Hello Tanker, Mitchell, Hernandez:  Man, what passion, what words, what bull shit. Please hate my guts but don't put words in my mouth. I never spit upon a returning soldier or called anyone a baby killer.  I never ran. I stood my moral ground, which, yes, I think was higher than yours. I lived within and by the laws, something not all of you &quot;in country&quot; can claim.  Yes there was no &quot;peace&quot; or &quot;anti&quot; war movement, rather just a anti-nam movement that ended as quickly as the name war ended. Am I proud of that too? No.  But please, don't give me this scenario about poor little villagers welcomming the &quot;beau geste&quot; of the big white god fathers (please overlook the racist tones), where do you begin to draw the real lines of Viet Nam? When the French were kicked out, or the Chinese?  The historical facts regarding your &quot;po little villagers&quot; is quite different if you happen to be from Laos or Thailand, or other parts Asian. Please don't try and rewrite history in Christian Dogma either.  <br>
The simple fact is that Viet Nam was a total and tragic mistake, regardless of any &quot;re-framing&quot; you wish to do now, 30 years too late.  What would have happen to all those dead, in Laos, Cambodia (no thanks to Pol Pot OR the CIA) and Viet Nam, both North and South, had NONE OF YOU gone?  That is the simple message that I am &quot;talking down electronically to you&quot; (and I don't mean that).  We, and the historians, can debate the other issues till the cows come home, and by the way, how many soldiers were REALLY spit upon by civilians, a dozen or two?  Are you perhaps, buying into the media hype just a wee bit too much?   Chatting with poor and starving people does not make one an expert in a culture that has been at war for over 100 years, and will probably say anything to you because of your nationality, Tanker.<br>
I don't condone the death of one man, or woman, or burning kids on the cover of Time magazine, let alone the millions killed by U.S. Citizens, Communist from the North (who had the absolute right to see Americans as invaders, mass lunatics like Pol Pot, CIA and it's many &quot;dark and wet&quot; deeds, or any of it, Saigon leadership included.  We, meaning American soldiers, should never have been there. PERIOD.  <br><br>
Think about our civil war, if your were a Northern and the French had decided to join the South and fight with and for them, I doubt that you would be pro french, oui?  The Vietnamese struggle was THEIR struggle, not ours.  I don't know about you, but now I get to live just south of Little Saigon, and see 1000's of them now over running all over my county.  Complete with their cafe' society, murdering youngsters, drive by shootings, (they have a fondness for automatic weapons), gangs like the &quot;nip boys&quot; and what I believe is a culture that absolutely has not the faintess idea about what honesty means, or what a lie is.  Am I a racist, probably, but more likely, a realist.  So the next time you want to make a grand gesture, or another &quot;beau geste&quot; send your own daughter or son, but I will be damned if you will get mine. That goes for Bosnia, Haiti, Africa, or Korea too.  <br><br>
The real fight is here, in America, the question that worries me is where will misguided soldiers like you end up, which side will you be on when OUR country is at risk?  That time is now.   Good nite Lads.
